<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0167 </DOCNO><TEXT>The diagnostic efficacy of I-131-MIGB scintigraphy for detection of localizedpheochromocytoma was studied in patients with this disease and 15 otherpatients suspected of pheochromocytoma. Five of the six patients withpheochromocytoma were true positive, while the other one was false negative.Fifteen suspected cases were true negative and none was false positive.The rate of sensitivity was 83.3 %, specificity 100 % and accuracy 95% in diagnosis using this method, thus showing that MIBG scintigraphyis highly useful for diagnosis of localized pheochromocytoma.</TEXT></DOC>